content: and welcome to ORC analysis lesson
today the GM was supposed to be Aurora perhaps ? but something came up
yy had troubles finding a replacement and so I agreed to keep something
and if you don't know yet, I am Samuli ( SamSite )
in such a short time, it was hard to prepare much for you, I'm afraid
so I will show you almost all my games from the 2nd Finnish Championship tournament played some 3 weeks ago
we will analyse what I did wrong at each given moment :)

Yue, slamduk, Liuchao, wolfzhou, Torsten, Samsone, slappanu, xiaoxiaohua, chess, blueice, danfengyue, hobbang, yysanyue, scotie, Ikon, yyfcsd, snowdrop, skywalker, akira, sosei, dreamy, Renju_liu_t, mima, tianxia, Whiz, ouyang, xuwu, Padovan, yaya, xinxin, kawamura, whte, tommy, yboil, yuelee00, xiaoxin, Joe1980cn, coco_yuang, lkogr.
In this year's tour, we had sadly only 5 players: me, Jussi Ikonen ( Morden ), Kari Haikonen ( nologic), Lauri Toivonen ( zathras at gameserver),
since players were short, we replaced it by more games: double round robin
I was unbeaten in domestic tournaments
and also won all games against other Finnish players in foreign tours also
this year, I had poor touch in playing, and did not expect much
and this is what happened, almost very badly
I was a bit worried he had seen some of my analysis here in other games
he played same 17th as in my previous games
I still went the same way,
and his 19th was not the best
I can not recall detailly how much I calculated here
but my attack was as shown
maybe it is for homework then ? :))
maybe no sure win but white will have a big advantage
maybe white advantage too large with 23 - m11 ...
ok, we will leave this for homework consideration :)
I could not see reason for this, so I just closed
I was ready to go up and win easily within some moves
but I was afraid of some black counter below
I was tired, since it was morning :) so I played more peacefully
I took the danger point myself
I knew he was forced to follow anyway
so no harm could be done
white has enough power to win anywhere now
and white has easy VCT, any volunteers ?
2nd game I recall was with Jussi ( Morden )
I decided to lead Jussi into a variant played by me and Ants at Renju Offline some days earlier
although, in that game I was lucky enough to win Ants as black,
I felt I could play it as white peacefully
what is possibly the best black plan
this seems not so good to black
white can not attack much by going up, so down is best
21 is also best choice I think
here is often played nowadays some games
I felt like I should not go into crazy attack
I thought Jussi would follow since he has no clear attack
creating some threat to right side
and I got strong attack on left and won fast
Jussi's 29 was not so direct help to right wing
and started to build attack in too fast pace
I had wasted some materials by playing too quick
ended up kind of a flat
perhaps white doesn't have strong basis after 29 yet
from here on, the game went on with quick moves
we were both pretty low on time
I spent time here, but found nothing
finally, after about 100 moves, Jussi won the game
it was first loss to me in almost 2 years against another Finnish player
and due to our tight schedule,
the next game started soon after

hobbang, danfengyue, slamduk, nu723, Torsten, skywalker, dreamy, Yue, whte, slappanu, Samsone, yuelee00, Whiz, Ikon, snowdrop, scotie, mima, xinxin, wolfzhou, xiaoxiaohua, chess, ouyang, tianxia, yboil, Liuchao, yyfcsd, yaya, Joe1980cn, akira, lkogr, Padovan, xiaoxin, xuwu, Renju_liu_t, yysanyue, kawamura.
this time I played with Kari ( nologic ), and I expected D3 again to be played
and played the older 7th, if can say so
here the game was decided already
I had no memory of all the victories, basically none of them :)
I knew this 12th to be win
and figured, I would find some win within the time limit
12-k7 would've been risky, as I would not have known it so well
I mean the outcome of the move
was it killer21st lesson about white win here?
I think killer put a file to Forum once
but I had not viewed it lately at that time :))
but since I knew it is win
and that likely white wins often by fouls
mainly it is done by forbidden moves
here white can win by 3x3, who can show, say me ?
good, it is easy. Thank you
so I got a win after my crushing loss
and might've been on a road to renewing my championship
knowing Lauri is not at his best in direct variations
but he was the one who surprised
I saw this move, and thought "oh good, it's this one"
here is how I saw it on board
I firstly remembered "oh it's the one where you block the diagonals on lower side
this is not what I was going for
I was thinking, this is not at all what I wanted
shouldn't 10 go inside the structure here?
g8 or i7 I don't know for sure
let's go back to it in short while
in my confusion I went here
and again I felt like what am I doing
then I thought ok, this 16 covers it
all was due to the confusion of 10th move
10th at g8 is not so familiar to me
I don't think the 10-i6 was a losing move, but
playing wrongly by mirror effect confused me
it was a mental shock, and I was still thinking about my loss earlier
and then I got another one
After 1st day I had only 2 points, and Jussi lead with 3points
and planned surprising opening to him
I played 10th so in hope of him starting a brave attack
"is there win?"  " what if there isn't?"
he was worried he can't find win,and gives me several useful stones
what do you think by looking, can black win by VCT ?
so it was instict, later proven correct? :)
here was the dilemma of Kari's
he must see the final win before making any moves
I could not see the win myself during the game
basic problem in winning is what ?
I would say it is sequence
sometimes we see how win might come
but ruin it by playing in the wrong order
yes, and cuts are often, though not alywa,s a consequence of wrong sequence in attack
after 22, it looked like white is free of danger
black is cornered and used lots of time
the attack was a failure and white wins eventually
I gave him active lines and said "go on, try"
but I needed 4 wins on 2nd day
even one draw could've destroyed my plans
I had to win, since he was threatening to win the championship
I knew he would open i5
and I knew he knows 4-g9 better than me
so I took it out of play
forced him to a battle in variant where we are both clueless
so it went, and I was pleased
not so theoretical as the other 4th
Jussi chose a bit closer attack
manipulating him in playing 15th here, I had a feeling he would play so
with 16th I planned this position to appear
and lots of space to win
and I thought Jussi fears me anyway
he would think I have something below
he won't dare to go here
and if he does, would he necessarily win
I was correct and he came down
now, the left side is not so dangerous
I was getting control of the whole board after a little risky thinking with 16th and 18th
I knew he would fear the overline chance
my plans were on top side
to block on left side or right side or middle
39th gave me chance to try win on left side
in this game I continued my brave tactics
and played more by feeling than calculation
and manipulated their playing in some level with my moves
white is not dead yet perhaps
white has tricky ways here in defence
but I didn't need to worry about this
of course, it was luck too :)
unfortunately I have no memory of my 2nd game with Lauri
but this is what we played :))
Lauri offered me same variant as earlier
and this time I remembered my plan correctly
I won the game finally playing pretty well, and I was on the way to winning the title
I faced Marko, and knowing him I opened D11, which he hates more than anything

Yue, yuelee00, Samsone, skywalker, lkogr, hobbang, slamduk, MIMI, slappanu, dreamy, Whiz, Ikon, Shangjin, mima, jiaren, Torsten, danfengyue, bergamot, nu723, scotie, wolfzhou, yboil, snowdrop, xinxin, yaya, xuwu, Joe1980cn, Padovan, xiaoxiaohua, yysanyue, xiaoxin, ouyang, tianxia, chess, whte.
I sensed that he would not play blacks, since his tournament had gone poorly
I did not know his knowledge here
but I know, that the more diredt the variant is,
the easier it is to get him confused somehow
here black has many lines open
though it is not a win position
so I got the upper-hand now
I am comfortable, he is annoyed :))
he played 18th, which is new to me, do you know this move ?
hobbang, can you say is it better for either color ?
don't ask me, I don't know :)
it did look pretty good to me too
but I thought he played it by feeling, not by preivous experience
so I thought, how to play to make him more nervous ?
when you get nervous, you get likely to make for example useless fours
I knew he would wonder to make four or not
I thought, that maybe it would be better not to do it
the right side seems hard for black to balance so, that it could use the left side effectively first
but I had a feeling he would play it
now it got a bit easier for me
if white could threat right side
now, should H11 be not used,
white would have a threat here to win
it would make black's plans harder
I wanted to balance the right side and try to move to left side
here I knew MArko would have another moment
he chose the one with the four again
thinking H4_1 connection is not good to give to black
although it is not so big help even
I played calmly again to right side
Marko sensed, that right wing is safe
although it is an obvious move to attack with
maybe he calculated he can defend somehow
or maybe he played 38 as a manipulation to make me follow 38
maybe I need to go right after all
37 gives much extra power to black on left
3-f7 is useless if going to defend on right
black might still get enough power by taking E6 point
and therefore I was feared, that white will just defend with 36th
I managed to keep my title from last year by ending up with 6 points like Jussi,
which I knew after the win over Jussi would happen if we end up in same points
my 4 wins on 2nd day were the results of brave tactics and risking based on the fact, that I know well how many opponents were thinking during each given positions
it is an important factor in tournaments games
if the opponent is new to you, it is hard to know his thinking
this year's title was the results of much luck too
but winning something the hard way can actually feel better than a victory gotten exactly as planned
Our time together is finished for today,
I thank you all for coming
and hope I get more preparation time to my next lesson
